        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/claudia-sheinbaum-rejects-trump-us-troops-mexico-drug-trafficking.png" alt="Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum said that US President Donald Trump proposed sending American troops into Mexico to help her administration fight drug trafficking" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum said that US President Donald Trump proposed sending American troops into Mexico to help her administration fight drug trafficking. Credits: AP Photo/Fernando Llano</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum has resisted Trump’s pressure to allow “<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-deeper-us-military-involvement" target="_blank">deeper US military involvement</a>” to fight drug cartels. She insisted that their sovereignty is not for trade and that their territory is inviolable. Sheinbaum asserted the need for collaboration, but each from their own territory. </p>
         
        
