          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇸🇪 Sweden plans to pay migrants $36,000 to exit</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           Sweden <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-may-25-worldwide-h1-7-plans-to-raise" target="_blank">plans to raise</a> the monetary aid for migrants who choose to return to their home countries from €900 ($1015) to €32,000 ($36,150), aiming to address ongoing integration challenges. PM Ulf Kristersson said the move is inspired by Denmark’s model and is intended for those who legally reside in Sweden but struggle to integrate or prefer to exit.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The current return program has had minimal triumph, with just one in 70 applications approved in 2023. Kristersson admits the policy won't appeal to everyone, but emphasized the need to regain control over migration. The proposal, set to take effect on January 1, 2026, is part of Sweden’s broader efforts to ease integration burdens and reduce long-term migration-related tensions.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
