        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇧🇩 Bangladesh Islamists oppose women’s rights</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Many Hefazat-e-Islam supporters rallied in Dhaka, Bangladesh, against the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-may-25-worldwide-h2-8-proposed-judicial-reforms" target="_blank">proposed judicial reforms</a>, such as:</p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-table font-family="Roboto+Serif" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" padding="10px 18px 10px 18px" style=" width:100%;">
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">→</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The recommendation proposed equal rights to women in property</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">→</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">They proposed to decriminalize commercial adult service work and recognize it as a profession</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">→</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Gender quotas in media and corporate boards</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">→</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">600-seat lower house with 300 seats reserved for women, alongside equal representation in an upper house</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">→</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Uniform family code to ensure equal rights for women in marriage, divorce, guardianship, and inheritance</td>
            </tr>
        </mj-table>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The group's leaders argued that these reforms go against Sharia law, especially Islamic inheritance rules. Over 20,000 demonstrators gathered near Dhaka University, carrying banners that rejected what they called "Western laws." 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Hefazat-e-Islam warned of nationwide protests on May 23 if their demands are ignored. Leader Mamunul Haque declared that the reforms not defy Sharia but threaten the religious fabric of Bangladesh.
          </p>
          </mj-text>
